DISTANCE LEARNING INPUT SURVEY--We’d like to reflect on our Distance Learning experience and use data to drive what Distance Learning may look like if we ever need to use this mode of instruction again.

We're looking to have Kenilworth-specific data and be better able to rely on our own school community’s thoughts and feedback to inform our practices and make changes as we (and if we) need to. The surveys will be live until June 30.

post_text:
Since she's so nice, let's honor her twice. (Oh, and it's Teacher Appreciation Week.)

Dedicated, compassionate, caring and kind. A few of many words that come to mind when describing Mrs. Ventura. Each and every day she's determined to make sure that each and every one of her students succeed. Her love for teaching is above and beyond and is expressed all the time in her actions! Not only is she an outstanding teacher in the classroom she is phenomenal guiding our children through distance learning. Her love for her students is beyond measure and our children are SO very lucky to have her as their teacher!

post_text:
Shout Out! to Mrs. Ventura!! From a thankful parent...

"Mrs. Ventura has been an amazing teacher during this unprecedented time. She has not only been excited to communicate with her students, but she has accommodated them and us parents in every single way. She quickly responds to email, she thoroughly explains things to the kids and parents with such patience and kindness. She has provided videos and lots of positive reinforcement for both academic learning and social emotional health as well! She is truly worth noting! We are honored to have her a part of our lives during this difficult time. She goes above and beyond to find engaging ways to teach!"

post_text:
Congratulations to Brearley High School's 19 seniors who were accepted to Kean University during yesterday's Instant Decision Day. Many received scholarships, including one FULL tuition scholarship!

"Just like it sounds, Instant Decision Day (or, as some call it ID Day) is a chance for high school students to reduce the entire admissions process (including, in some cases, financial or merit aid) to one day. If accepted, students then have until National Decision Day, May 1, of their senior year, to accept or refuse the admissions offer." (Taken from www.grownandflown.co) #BestYearYet

post_text: Schools will be operating on a delayed opening schedule, tomorrow, December 3rd to allow for the safe arrival of students and faculty and to address any potential refreezing issues. Doors will open at Brearley at 9:35AM, and Harding will begin at 10:00AM. Before-care is cancelled. AM PK begins at 10:00AM and PM PK begins at 1:00PM.

post_text:
Among other things, 21st Century learning is hallmarked by relevance, global connectivity, and technology enabled classrooms, like this one.

Fifth graders in Mrs. Jernigan's class connected with fellow 5th graders from Waywayseecappo School in Canada to discuss their Global Read Aloud book, _Front Desk_ by Kelly Yang. Students asked and responded to questions about the book. #Bestyearyet
